                        </graphic>
                     </figure>
                     18 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm001">NSM-001</ref> "The Faith of the Fathers"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm002">NSM-002</ref> "The Rite of the Holy Week"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm003">NSM-003</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm004">NSM-004</ref> "Homily of St. Michael"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm005">NSM-005</ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm006">NSM-006</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm007">NSM-007</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm008">NSM-008</ref> "Vita of Täklä Haymanot"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm009">NSM-009</ref> "The Book of the Matrimony Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm010">NSM-010</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm011">NSM-011</ref> "Prayer of Incense"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm012">NSM-012</ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm013">NSM-013</ref> "Synaxarion (September)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm014">NSM-014</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm015">NSM-015</ref> "Vita of Zarʾa Buruk"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm016">NSM-016</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm017">NSM-017</ref> "Vita of Kiros"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESnsm018">NSM-018</ref> "Prayer of Mary". Objects.</ab>
       
